dsDescriptionValue.value: This study investigated the scope of efforts to involve parents in family planning progress for teenagers. The study data come from a 1981 national survey of 351 Title X recipients conducted by the Family Planning council of Southeastern Pennsylvania, Inc.  Total cases: 351; total variables: 102.
